de. Offering a new paradigm of female performance that positions women at the core of public culture, Performing women is essential reading for scholars of pre-modern women and drama, and is also relevant to lecturers and students of late-medieval performance, religion and memory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aActresseszFrancezMetzxHistory. 0aDramay15th and 16th centuriesxHistory and criticism. 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 4aMedieval Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aJoan of Arc.  aMetz.  aMiddle Ages.  aSaint Catherine of Siena.  adrama.  agender.  aimpersonation.  aliturgy.  aperformance.  awomen.1 aCrowder, Susannah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packagez978311128277040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612724240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526127242423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526127242/original  a978-3-11-128277-0  Manchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packageb2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles